  printf(active_format.c_str(), user_input);
printf uses active_format (loaded from config via set_runtime_log_format) as the format string, with user_input as a variadic argument. If an attacker can modify the config file to set log_format to a malicious string (e.g., "Hello %n%n%n"), the printf call interprets user_input as format specifiers, enabling arbitrary memory writes.

